[[File:Петр Горлов 1904.jpg|thumb|200px]] '''Pyotr Nikolayevich Gorlov''' ({{lang-ru|Пётр Никола́евич Го́рлов}}; 11 May 1839 in [[Irkutsk]], Irkutsk Governorate, [[Russian Empire]] – 20 November 1915) was a [[geologist]] and engineer who explored coal deposits in the [[Donets Basin]], the [[Caucasus]], [[Central Asia]] and [[Ussuri Krai]]. He founded the city of [[Horlivka]]; the city has a monument in honor of him.<ref>{{cite web|title=Horlivka - Birthplace and Home of Cosmonaut Alexander Volkov|url=http://www.ukraine.com/donetsk-oblast/horlivka/|work=Ukraine.com|publisher=NewMedia Holdings|accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Marples|first=David|title=The most dangerous workplace in the world: Ukraine's coal mines|url=http://www.ukrweekly.com/old/archive/2002/430204.shtml|accessdate=31 May 2014|newspaper=The Ukrainian Weekly|date=October 27, 2002|volume=70 |number=43}}</ref>
